title: Gyroelongated triangular bicupola
summary: In geometry, the gyroelongated triangular bicupola is one of the Johnson solids  (J44). As the name suggests, it can be constructed by gyroelongating a triangular bicupola (either triangular orthobicupola, J27, or the cuboctahedron) by inserting a hexagonal antiprism between its congruent halves.
